<HEADLINE> Kings' Abdul-Wahad Undergoes Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sacramento Kings guard Tariq  
Abdul-Wahad underwent arthroscopic surgery Friday to repair a minor 
cartilage tear in his left knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Abdul-Wahad injured the knee while playing for the French  
National Team during the 1999 European Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	The 20-minute procedure by team physician Dr. Richard Marder was  
successful, and Abdul-Wahad will be able to resume his offseason 
training within three weeks, the team said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-6 Abduh-Wahad averaged 9.3 points, 3.8 rebounds and  
one assist as the Kings' starting shooting guard last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
