<HEADLINE> Brazil 2, New Zealand 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GUADALAJARA, Mexico (AP) -- Marcos Paulo and Ronaldinho scored  
goals Friday night as Brazil coasted to a 2-0 victory over New 
Zealand in the Confederations Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Marcos Paulo scored in the 44th minute when his kick sailed over  
the head of New Zealand goalie Michael Utting. Ronaldinho fired a 
free kick into the goal in the 87th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Brazil had already qualified for the Confederations Cup  
semifinals, and New Zealand had already been eliminated. Brazil 
will play Saudi Arabia in a Sunday semifinal match here, and Mexico 
will play the United States in Mexico City. The final is Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Brazil played without such regulars as Odvan, Serginho and  
Vampeta, and Ronaldinho played only in the second half. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
