<HEADLINE> Doug Flutie Recording Album </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) -- First came Flutie Flakes. Now there's the  
Flutie CD. 
</P>
<P>
	Doug Flutie, quarterback of the Buffalo Bills, has been  
recording an album with his rock band, The Flutie Gang. It will 
feature nine original songs and will be released by Frequency 
Records in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
	Part of the proceeds will benefit the Doug Flutie Jr. Foundation  
for Autism. His popular ``Flutie Flakes'' cereal also benefited the 
foundation. 
</P>
<P>
	Flutie, whose son suffers from autism, said being the drummer in  
a rock band is a lot like being a quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think in each you have the ability to control tempo,''  
Flutie said this week. ``You have a big say in whether a play or a 
piece succeeds.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Flutie isn't giving up his day job -- he reports to Buffalo Bills  
training camp today. But he loves his side interest. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a great release for me,'' Flutie said. ``Football is my  
profession. This is my hobby.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
