<HEADLINE> Lightning Re-Sign Nylander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Lightning re-signed center  
Michael Nylander to a one-year contract Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Nylander, 26, scored two goals and added seven assists in 24  
games with the Lightning after being acquired from the Calgary 
Flames in January. 
</P>
<P>
	``Michael is an extremely talented offensive player who has  
proven he can produce at a top level, both in the National Hockey 
League and internationally,'' Lightning general manager Rick Dudley 
said. ``He's an intelligent player who provides us with an 
important offensive dimension.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Nylander, a 5-foot-11, 195-pound native of Stockholm, Sweden,  
was the 59th overall pick by the Hartford Whalers in the 1991 entry 
draft. He was dealt to Calgary in 1994 and appeared in 168 games 
with the Flames, scoring 34 goals and adding 74 assists. 
</P>
<P>
	He has been a member of Sweden's national team seven times,  
including five world championships appearances, the 1996 World Cup 
team and the 1998 Olympic team. 
  	   	
