<HEADLINE> Worker Kills Boss, Self in N.C. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- A maintenance worker entered a trucking  
terminal Friday, warned other workers to ``get out of the way,'' 
and shot and killed his supervisor before killing himself. 
</P>
<P>
	``He had a specific target,' said Charlotte-Mecklenburg police  
spokesman Keith Bridges. ``He intended to kill him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The supervisor died at the scene and the gunman was transported  
to Carolinas Medical Center, where he died about 3 1/2 hours after the 
noon shooting. 
</P>
<P>
	The names of the victims were being withheld until family  
members were contacted, Bridges said. 
</P>
<P>
	The motive for the shooting was under investigation, Bridges  
said. But workers at the west Charlotte company said the gunman had 
been having problems with his supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told me the supervisor was messing with him,'' said Derrick  
Hooker, who said he spoke with the maintenance worker Friday 
morning. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
