<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 20:10:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 8 Food Stands Close at Safeco Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Seattle Mariners and catering contractor  
Volume Services shut down eight Safeco Field concessions stands 
before Friday's game with the Baltimore Orioles because of 
equipment problems, team spokesman Randy Adamack said. 
</P>
<P>
	King County inspectors found dozens of health-code violations  
during two inspections of concession stands during the Mariners' 
first homestand at the new $517 million stadium. A July 22 
inspection found 26 ``red critical'' violations, meaning they had 
to be immediately corrected because they posed the threat of 
illness. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mariners and Volume Services were hoping to avoid costly  
``third strike'' violations during their second homestand, which 
began Friday. Concessions workers and managers underwent food 
service retraining while the team was on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	Adamack said the Mariners hope to re-open the eight closed food  
stands by Saturday's game, but weren't sure that would be possible 
because of a 1 p.m. PDT start time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
