Thompson, the head of its capital markets unit, will become 
president, replacing John Georgius, who will retire at the end of 
the year. 

</P>
<P>
 *Merck &AMP; Co., up 7/8 at 67 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reported that the company's scientists  
are laying plans to begin the first human tests of two promising 
experimental AIDS vaccines. 

</P>
<P>
 *ARM Financial Group Inc., down 4 3/4 at 5    	
</P>
<P>
	The Louisville, Ky.-based ARM Financial reported a  
second-quarter net loss of $174 million, or $7.30 a share, as it 
moves to restructure its institutional business. The company sells 
guaranteed investment contracts to institutions, as well as 
annuities and other retirement savings products to individuals. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
 *Lam Research Corp., up 9 at 55 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Fremont, Calif., maker of equipment used to build circuits  
on computer chips reported earnings for its fiscal fourth quarter 
that topped Wall Street analysts' estimates. 

</P>
<P>
 *Gilead Sciences, up 9 3/16 at 77 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The Foster City, Calif., biopharmaceutical company late Thursday  
reported a second-quarter loss of 48 cents a share, only a penny 
better than the same period a year ago but better than the loss of 
53 cents that Wall Street analysts had expected. 

</P>
<P>
 *Noodle Kidoodle Inc., down 1 7/8 at 4 7/16    	
</P>
