this year to form noodlekidoodle.com, an Internet joint venture 
with former NewGrocer CEO Daniel Nissan. As a result of the 
investment, the company expects second-quarter losses to be wider 
than Wall Street analysts' estimates. 

</P>
<P>
 *ANB Corp., up 4 1/8 at 32 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Old National Bancorp signed a definitive agreement to merge with  
ANB in a transaction currently valued at about $212.4 million. Old 
National of Evansville, Ind., said it expects to record a $7 
million charge against 1999 earnings in connection with the merger. 




  	   	
