<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Ties Sosa With 38th Homer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire tied Sammy Sosa for the major  
league lead with 38 home runs and set a record for most homers in a 
five-year span when he hit one in the sixth inning of St. Louis' 
game against Colorado on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a 1-0 pitch from Pedro Astacio into the right-field  
bullpen to lead off the sixth for his 11th homer in 15 games to cut 
the Rockies' lead over the Cardinals to 3-2. He has 257 homers the 
last five years, breaking the record he shared with Babe Ruth, who 
hit 256 from 1926-30. 
</P>
<P>
	The homer was the 495th of his career. He's also one away from  
tying his own record for most homers in four straight seasons. He 
hit 219 from 1995-98. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has hit 480 homers as a first baseman, tying him for  
second place on the career list with Jimmie Foxx. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has two career homers in 14 at-bats against Astacio,  
among the league leaders in homers allowed with 25. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa hit his 38th earlier in the day, connecting off Masato  
Yoshii of the New York Mets. He has 282 homers with the Cubs, tying 
Ryne Sandberg for the fourth-highest in team history. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
