<HEADLINE> Russia To Get $640 Million From IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- Russia will receive the first installment of a  
$4.5 billion loan from the International Monetary Fund on Sunday, 
Russia's Finance Ministry said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	But the $640 million will be used to make a loan repayment to  
the IMF that falls due on the same day, the ministry said. 
</P>
<P>
	The IMF loan deal, announced Wednesday, was an enormous relief  
for the government. It owes the IMF about $18 billion and has 
struggled to stay current on its debts to the fund since its 
economic meltdown last August. 
</P>
<P>
	That crash saw much-needed international lending grind to a halt  
and sent the economy into a tailspin. 
</P>
<P>
	The IMF loan is Russia's first major credit since the August  
crash. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
