<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 14:30:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pats' Woody, Katzenmoyer Reach Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The New England Patriots agreed Friday to  
contracts with their remaining two draft picks, first-rounders 
Damien Woody and Andy Katzenmoyer. 
</P>
<P>
	Woody, a Boston College center taken with the 17th pick of the  
draft, agreed to a contract estimated at $1.25 million a year for 
five years with a $3.85 million signing bonus. 
</P>
<P>
	That left the Patriots under the salary cap by $835,000 a year,  
but there was no confirmation that Katzenmoyer, the Ohio State 
linebacker chosen with the 28th pick, received that as part of a 
four-year deal. 
</P>
<P>
	The Patriots hope that Woody, a three-year starter in college,  
can start in place of Dave Wohlabaugh, who left for Cleveland as a 
free agent. Katzenmoyer also may see significant time in his first 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	New England also signed two free agents -- cornerback Nate Brooks  
of Miami and kicker Marcus Williams of Arizona State, who played 
with the Rhein Fire in NFL Europe. Williams had been in the Arizona 
Cardinals camp. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
