<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Allied Waste Sells Some Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. (AP) -- Allied Waste Industries Inc. agreed to  
sell some of its operations to Republic Services Inc. of Fort 
Lauderdale, Fla., for $230 million in cash. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement, announced Thursday, satisfies part of the Justice  
Department's requirement that Allied Waste divest itself of some 
assets before acquiring Browning-Ferris Industries Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	The current sale includes four landfill operations, 11 transfer  
stations and several commercial hauling operations in seven states. 
The combined revenue is $123 million. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
