<HEADLINE> E. Africa Broadcast Network Planned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania (AP) -- A Tanzanian media executive  
announced plans today to start the first East African regional 
broadcasting network by the end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	Reginald Mengi, chief of the IPP Media, said he has received  
broadcasting licenses from neighboring Kenya and Uganda. 
</P>
<P>
	The new TV and radio network would broadcast mostly in  
Kiswahili, the widely spoken language of the three countries, Mengi 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	He said that he has received permission from the government of  
Kenya to broadcast in Nairobi, Mombasa and Kisumu and from the 
Ugandan government to broadcast in Kampala. 
</P>
<P>
	Mengi owns a chain of 11 newspapers, two television channels and  
two radio stations as well as beverage, soap and petroleum jelly 
companies. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
