<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Michigan Company Recalls Hams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) -- A pork and beef processor and distributor  
is recalling 130 pounds of ham products that might be contaminated 
with bacteria. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dearborn Sausage Co. products being recalled are whole and  
half spiral hams with glaze packets and red netting, produced July 
20 with the company brand label. 
</P>
<P>
	Testing by the U.S. Department of Agriculture on a sample from  
the company's slicing room found the bacteria, listeria 
monocytogenes, the company said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Listeria bacteria can cause fever, headaches, nausea and can  
lead to death. 
</P>
<P>
	Dearborn Sausage decided to recall all products processed in the  
slicing room on the day the sample was taken. None of the product 
lot from which the sample was drawn was shipped, and of remaining 
products, the company has recovered all but the 130 pounds of ham. 
</P>
<P>
	Recall products have lot numbers of H56194B, G76196A and  
H56194A. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
