<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stifling heat and humidity continued to choke much of the  
Midwest and East on Friday, while temperatures in the West remained 
below normal. 
</P>
<P>
	The mercury neared 100 degrees in many places in the Plains, the  
Mississippi Valley, the Southeast and the mid-Atlantic region. 
</P>
<P>
	A few showers and thunderstorms were seen across central Kansas,  
northern Nebraska, the Dakotas, Wisconsin and Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	Strong thunderstorms with hail and strong winds hit West  
Virginia and western Virginia. A few isolated thunderstorms were 
also seen along the Gulf coast and Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	Utah, Nevada and other spots in the Southwest experienced light  
to moderate showers. Farther north, the Pacific Northwest and 
northern Rockies were mainly clear and dry. Temperatures remained 
in the 70s and 80s, well below normal for the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures Thursday in the lower 48 states ranged from a high  
of 108 in Hobart, Okla., to a morning low of 38 in Stanley, Idaho. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
