<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Irvine Confident for German GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOCKENHEIM, Germany (AP) -- Eddie Irvine has good reason to be  
confident for the German Grand Prix. 
</P>
<P>
	He drove his Ferrari to the second-fastest time over two  
practices Friday, beaten only by Italy's Jarno Trulli in a 
Prost-Peugeot. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine is trying to become the first Ferrari driver to win the  
championship in 20 years. He trails defending champion Mika 
Hakkinen by two points in the Formula One drivers' standings and 
will take the lead by winning the race. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine held the fastest time most of the day, until Trulli beat  
it by a half second with new tires late in the afternoon session. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine's performance was spoiled by a wild spin out of a curve.  
</P>
<P>
	``It was my fault that I spun and then the engine cut out,'' the  
British driver said. ``It was a shame because the car was going 
well.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine became Ferrari's No. 1 driver when Michael Schumacher  
broke his leg at the British GP three weeks ago. In his first race 
as the new team leader, Irvine won the Austrian GP last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel under less pressure here,'' Irvine said. ``Now I am  
more confident and content and I hope that will come through in my 
driving.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 4.2-mile Hockenheim course is one of the fastest on the  
circuit, with long straightaways that should favor the powerful 
engines of McLaren-Mercedes cars driven by Hakkinen and David 
Coulthard. 
</P>
<P>
	Coulthard had the fourth-fastest time, but Hakkinen was only  
10th. Hakkinen won last year's race ahead of Coulthard. 
</P>
<P>
	Coulthard, who bumped into Hakkinen in the first lap in Austria,  
said he was trying to get a feel for the car on the fast circuit. 
</P>
<P>
	By knocking Hakkinen off the course in Austria, Coulthard may  
have cost McLaren a victory. Coulthard finished second there and 
Hakkinen was third. 
</P>
<P>
	``Both Mika's mind and my mind will be sharpened at the start of  
the race if we are close to each other,'' Coulthard said. ``But 
it's finished.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Coulthard said the McLarens may not be so dominant this year.  
</P>
<P>
	``If you look at a year ago, we had a bigger, better package  
than we do this year,'' he said. ``Having a lot of power and a lot 
of speed is only one part of the lot. It's still important to go 
through the whole complex.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Trulli was timed in 1 minute, 45.677 seconds, .548 seconds ahead  
of Irvine, whose best lap of 1:46.225 came in the afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	``I like this circuit very much since I drove here a lot in  
Formula Three and in six races, I won six times,'' Trulli said. 
``It is good for the morale to start the weekend in this way.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
