<HEADLINE> Browns Sign Free-Agent QB Thad Busby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEREA, Ohio (AP) -- The Cleveland Browns, looking for another  
quarterback after John Dutton broke his foot in training camp this 
week, signed free-agent quarterback Thad Busby on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Busby was signed by San Francisco as an undrafted free agent  
last year but was cut during training camp. 
</P>
<P>
	Busby, 24, was the Atlantic Coast Conference offensive player of  
the year in 1997 at Florida State. He ranks fourth in school 
history with 411 completions. 
</P>
<P>
	Dutton, who was competing for the team's third-string  
quarterback spot, broke a bone in his left foot during drills and 
will be in a cast for four weeks. 
  	   	
</P>
