<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Indians' Ramirez in Car Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WESTLAKE, Ohio (AP) -- Cleveland Indians outfielder Manny Ramirez  
was involved in a minor four-car accident Thursday night but no one 
was hurt or cited in the accident. It wasn't clear whether Ramirez 
was driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Police Capt. Guy Turner said today that he had few details on  
the accident. Two vehicles were towed but no one was hurt and no 
ambulance was dispatched. 
</P>
<P>
	It wasn't clear whether the 27-year-old Ramirez was driving or a  
passenger, Turner said. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident occurred along a two-lane road where construction  
crews have been installing sidewalks. Turner said it was unlikely 
the crew was working after dark when the accident occurred in this 
upscale suburb 10 miles west of Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	Details of the accident must await the completion of an approved  
report by the investigating officer, who was due back on duty for 
the evening shift today, Turner said. He said he could not provide 
information from the officer's notes at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramirez is hitting .325 and leads the AL with 106 RBIs.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
