<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Indians' Ramirez Unhurt in Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WESTLAKE, Ohio (AP) -- Cleveland Indians slugger Manny Ramirez  
escaped injury when his car was hit from the rear in a four-car 
chain-reaction accident. 
</P>
<P>
	No one was hurt or cited in the Thursday night accident, police  
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Pat Roche, prosecutor in this Cleveland suburb, was reviewing  
the case to decide whether to file charges. Police Capt. Guy Turner 
ruled out alcohol as a factor. 
</P>
<P>
	Turner said Ramirez had stopped behind a car waiting to turn  
left across traffic when his auto was hit from the rear. Ramirez 
then got pushed into the first car. 
</P>
<P>
	The front two cars, including Ramirez's, could be driven away  
but the rear cars had to be towed. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramirez was hitting .325 and leading the American League with  
106 RBIs entering Friday night's game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
