<HEADLINE> 20 Hurt in Ill. Tour Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DOWNERS GROVE, Ill. (AP) -- Twenty people were injured, some  
critically, after a car slammed into the back of a tour bus and 
caused it to tip over, ejecting several passengers, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident happened about 10 p.m. Friday on Interstate 355 in  
suburban Chicago, said Master Sgt. Luis Tigera of the Illinois 
state police. 
</P>
<P>
	The car's driver was among the injured. At least 15 people were  
taken to local hospitals. Six had life-threatening injuries, said 
Sue Sullivan, a nursing supervisor at Good Samaritan Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear where the 20-seat bus was from and where it was  
headed. 
  	   	
