<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Middlesex Drive Wins at Saratoga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Middlesex Drive led throughout  
Friday to score a neck victory in Saratoga's feature, the 41st 
running of the $150,000 Grade II Bernard Baruch Handicap for horses 
3-years-old and older. 
</P>
<P>
	Tangazi was second in the field of nine, a half-length before  
Comic Strip. 
</P>
<P>
	Rather then chance being caught in traffic, Shane Sellers sent  
Middlesex Drive to the lead early and, despite being hard pressed 
throughout, the 4-year-old colt by Pine Bluff-York Woods stuck it 
out for the win. 
</P>
<P>
	Middlesex Drive carried 117 and Shane Sellers 1 1/8 miles in 1:46.2  
on the firm Mellon Turf Course to earn $90,000 for C. Steven 
Duncker with his second win in five starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $5.70, $3.30 and $2.40. Tangazi paid $4.30  
and $2.80, and Comic Strip was $2.70. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
