<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Suns Sign Top Pick Shawn Marion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The Phoenix Suns signed first-round draft pick  
Shawn Marion on Friday to a four-year deal worth just under $5 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	The salary was the most allowed for Marion, the No. 9 pick  
overall, under the NBA's collective bargaining agreement. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-7 Marion played forward in his only season at UNLV,  
but the Suns expect him to be a shooting guard, matching his 
athletic skills and speed with point guard Jason Kidd's ability to 
run the court. Marion is not known as a great outside shooter, 
though the Suns believe that can improve over time. 
</P>
<P>
	Marion is playing for the Suns' entry in the Salt Lake City  
Summer League. He scored a team-high 23 points and grabbed 11 
rebounds in the team's loss 89-82 loss to Houston Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Marion averaged 18.7 points and 9.3 rebounds at UNLV, shooting  
.529 from the field. 
</P>
<P>
	The Suns also signed second-year guard Toby Bailey to a one-year  
contract. Terms weren't disclosed. Bailey averaged 2.9 points and 2 
rebounds last season in limited playing time. He missed 15 games 
because of knee injuries. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
