<HEADLINE> Gunman Shoots Officer in Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- A man in police custody at a hospital  
took an officer's gun Friday and shot him before barricading 
himself in a bathroom and committing suicide. 
</P>
<P>
	Wallace Bolus, 35, had been arrested earlier in the day on bad  
check charges at a bookstore near Florida State University. 
</P>
<P>
	He was brought to Tallahassee Memorial Hospital after apparently  
having some sort of seizure. 
</P>
<P>
	He was escorted to the hospital's restroom by Florida State  
University police Officer Christopher Lee. Bolus wrested Lee's gun 
away and shot the officer in the arm, Tallahassee Police spokesman 
Kevin Bradshaw said. He fatally shot himself during a 45-minute 
standoff. 
</P>
<P>
	Lee was in satisfactory condition Friday evening.  
</P>
<P>
	Bolus had a criminal history in Kentucky dating back a dozen  
years and was wanted on sexual assault, sodomy and first degree 
felony assault warrants, said Liz Hirst, a Florida Department of 
Law Enforcement spokeswoman. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
