<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bengals Camp Opens Without Pickens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GEORGETOWN, Ky. (AP) -- The Cincinnati Bengals opened training  
camp Friday without star receiver Carl Pickens or either of the 
team's top two draft picks. 
</P>
<P>
	All of the absences were expected, however. Pickens said he will  
sit out this season and give up his $3.5 million salary, rather 
than play for the Bengals again. Quarterback Akili Smith and 
cornerback Charles Fisher have not come to terms with the team. 
</P>
<P>
	Wide receiver Craig Yeast, the fourth-round draft pick from  
Kentucky, will get a tryout as a punt returner, coach Bruce Coslet 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We'll see how much he can handle,'' Coslet said.  
</P>
<P>
	Pickens, the Bengals' career leading receiver, was at home  
hoping to be traded. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's living in Atlanta, working out every day, staying ready,  
waiting for something to happen,'' his agent Steve Zucker said 
Thursday. ``If it doesn't, he's prepared to retire.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, the third overall pick in this year's draft, was in San  
Diego while his agent tried to bridge a philosophical gap with the 
Bengals. 
</P>
<P>
	General manager Mike Brown wants Smith to accept an  
incentive-laden deal like the one that running back Ricky Williams 
got from New Orleans. Agent Leigh Steinberg is looking for a deal 
along the lines of the one quarterback Tim Couch got from 
Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	``Basically, there's been no progress made since draft day,''  
Steinberg said. ``In recent years, we've had a very positive 
negotiating relationship, so this has been a real surprise.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Two players, guard Ken Blackman and linebacker Tom Tumulty,  
failed their pre-camp physicals and were placed on the 
active-physically unable to perform list. 
</P>
<P>
	Both are recovering from knee surgery and will have another  
chance to pass. Until then, they count against the team's 80-man 
roster and could be activated for practice upon passage of the 
physical. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
