<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-30 11:20:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Worker Murdered at N.C. Truck Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- One person was fatally shot Friday and  
another person wounded at a trucking terminal when an employee 
entered the building, fired at a colleague and then turned the gun 
on himself, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	It wasn't immediately clear which employee was killed at Watkins  
Motor Lines in west Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
	The shooter entered the building and ``allowed others to get out  
of the way,'' said Keith Bridges, a Charlotte-Mecklenburg Police 
Department spokesman. ``He then shot the other person before 
turning the gun on himself.'' 
</P>
<P>
	As for a motive, Bridges said: ``We're still looking into it.  
There was obviously something between the two.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Several terminal workers outside the plant said a maintenance  
worker shot his supervisor before shooting himself. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
