<HEADLINE> Stocks Higher in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are higher in early trading today.  
The Dow Jones Industrial Average is up seven points. Advancers on 
the New York Stock Exchange hold a nearly 2-1 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq is up 20 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index is up three  
points. There appears to be some upward momentum in the market to 
start the session. 
</P>
<P>
	But analysts warn that investors may not be done taking money  
off the table amid new concerns about higher interest rates. Bond 
prices are lower, and that may keep any early gains in check. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors got a fairly benign report today on June personal  
income and spending levels. 
</P>
<P>
	They're also standing by for an upcoming report this morning on  
June sales of new homes. 
  	   	
</P>
