<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Infant Clothing Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 68,000 infant ``creeper'' short-sleeved  
body suits are being recalled by Shopko Stores because they have 
defective snaps that can detach and choke children. 
</P>
<P>
	The Consumer Product Safety Commission said Thursday the suits  
have two snaps on the left shoulder and three snaps at the crotch 
that easily can be removed. 
</P>
<P>
	No injuries have been reported but ``the creepers should be  
returned to the store for a refund,'' said commission spokeswoman 
Nychelle Fleming. 
</P>
<P>
	Shopko Stores of Green Bay, Wis., sold the clothing,  
manufactured in solid and stripe fabrics, from last December to 
June for sizes newborn to 24 months. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
