<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed higher Friday with oil and  
banking shares leading the climb upwards. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, BP Amoco, the most heavily weighted stock in the Dow  
Jones Stoxx Index, rose 2.6 percent to close at 1,207 pence. While 
in Paris, Elf Aquitaine climbed 5 euros to 160 euros and Total Fina 
jumped 3.80 euros to finish at 119 euros. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Energy Index closed up 3.7 percent, making  
the sector the best performer of the day. 
</P>
<P>
	Not far behind was the Dow Jones Stoxx Bank Index, finishing  
with a 2.1 percent gain. Shares of Lloyds TSB rose 10 pence to 
close at 802 pence, after the bank announced a 16 percent rise in 
underlying first-half pretax profits. Lloyds attributed the gain to 
a healthy growth in the mortgages division and decreased costs. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 591 European companies rose 5.15  
points, or 1.7 percent, to close at 301.28 Friday, after a decline 
of 1.6 percent the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The index tumbled to its lowest level in four months Thursday on  
concern that the U.S. Federal Reserve will increase interest rates 
at its next meeting August 24. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in  
countries joining the single currency, closed up 4.52 points at 
312.35. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 58.43 points to 3638.62,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index was up 67.41 points at 3,623.91. 
</P>
<P>
	Among European bourses, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index gained 1.0  
percent to 5,101.87 and the Paris CAC-40 jumped 1.8 percent to 
4,382.06. The Paris index was helped by strong gains in oil and 
auto stocks. Renault rose 8.9 percent to 50.20 euros a share, while 
Peugeot jumped 2.8 percent to 161 euros. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, the FTSE 100 index rose 1.9 percent, to 6,231.9  
points. Milan's MIBtel index rose 2.0 percent to 32,584, while 
Amsterdam's AEX index jumped 1.2 percent to 552.77. 
  	   	
</P>
